			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">What do I do when there's a stubborn warrior?<a name="15635"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 14 04 2:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Today I grouped with a warrior that said that he should pull.  I told him that it would probably be better if I pulled instead of him since I can pull singles by lulling the mobs.  He got mad and started saying that he hates bards that think they are gods in dungeons and think that they should take over the warrior's place in pulling.  Well, obviously, the only time he could get singles is if it was the only/last one in the room.  So on average he would bring 3 mobs and since we didn't have an enchanter, I had to take over with mezzing.  Then he started saying that I need to play my haste song instead of mezzing.  About 4 times he pulled 5 mobs and I had to go all over the room just clicking and mezzing, so when we died when he pulled that many, he blamed it on me for not mezzing (like I didn't have to do enough stuff in the group already).  Then, finally, the whole group started yelling at him to let me pull so I can get singles, his response was still no.  Then he decided to waste the cleric's mana by having him lull the mobs that he had, instead of having me do it and not wasting any.  So my question is, what should I do to the warrior's that still think that they make the best pullers no matter what?</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
