OK I know it's not possible for some people to have guildmates or regular on-line EQ groups, but man the ONLY negative experiences I have had in LDON were in the one or two times I was grouped with strangers.  I departed from one group after we succeeded on a normal rescue in Mistmoore with ONLY 30 minutes to spare.  The SK tank, who incidentally was incapable of taking agro before I had taken about 500-600 damage per pull, basically said I was a coward and didn't pull fast enough.  I mean, at best, by being totally aggressive, I could have saved maybe 20 minutes.  If playing this game is so painful to him that 20 more minutes fighting in a dungeon ruins his day, he should find a new source of recreation.  I just don't do pickup groups.  Ever.</span></td>
