				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What do I do when there's a stubborn warrior?<a name="15818"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 15 04 7:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have had this happen to me a time or two when the tank thought he should pull.  In this case it was also a warrior, if it was a pally i wouldnt have had a to much of a problem with it since they can pacify.
<br />

<br />
The way i handled it was when the mob was at about 5% i would disengage from battle and lull the next room before he had a chance to pull anything.  In the event that i didnt get all mobs lulled then 2 mobs are easier to deal with then 5.
<br />

<br />
The tank did notice i was lulling during the adventure and tried to leave the mob to be finished off by the rest of the group but some mobs as he learned dont turn and walk away when low on hp's.
<br />

<br />
The post a few up from mine has alot of good tactics.  I suppose it all boils down to how much you want to put up with that stubborn person or how quick you can think of a way to pull everyone through the adventure with a win.
<br />

<br />
Silkworm</span></td>
