			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What do I do when there's a stubborn warrior?<a name="15867"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 16 04 9:55 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Whenever I am the sole CC for a group, I make it clear that will pull before we enter. If someone else insists on pulling, usually I leave.  Unless I know the person who wants to pull, and know he/she is capable of it.
<br />

<br />
Here is a little secret.
<br />
It isnt that hard to pull most LDoN adventures with any class. You have to do something very very stupid to get more then 3 adds on a pull.  Something like open a door and shoot or cast on a mob in the back of the room.  Or run down a hallway with mobs on either side to get at some named at the end.  
<br />
Anyone can walk into a room and hit the closest mob.  95% of the time in LDoN that will bring 1 or 2 ads.  I dont care what the composition of the group is  (as long as they have at least one healer). Any group that cant handle 2 adds has no business doing an LDoN dungeon.  It is that other 5%, the 6 add pulls, that require someone, or the entire group, to be on thier toes and make very few mistakes to survive.
<br />

<br />
That last 5% is why I like to pull.  Wiping sucks.
<br />

<br />
There are times when midstream someone decides to pull on thier own.  Usually it is a monk, rogue or paladin.  
<br />
I always ask them if they can Pacify AND escape aggro from a bad pull.  Of course no one can do both but a Bard.  
<br />
They usually get the picture.  But not always.
<br />
So then I ask them if they can gate a mob back to its spawn point and escape all aggro.  They cant do that either.  
<br />
Most are convinced by now, but some folks are stubborn, or stupid.
<br />
So then I ask if they have the ability to control any adds that come unseen or unintentionally.  They cant do that of course.
<br />
Now we are down to the folks who REEEEELY want to pull....
<br />
So I let em pull, and do my best to keep my group alive.  
<br />
More often then not, they do a fine job, and we win
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
