				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What do I do when there's a stubborn warrior?<a name="15908"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 16 04 12:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Lenowill,
<br />

<br />
Great thoughts, one issue however.
<br />

<br />
I have used MoM in LDoN many times before I got Requiem when I was the main slower.  The only times I did NOT use MoM when I was employing such tactics was when we had adds.  Here's why I did not use MoM with adds:
<br />

<br />
You slow 3 adds 45%, they will have no reason to attack anyone but you, even if they were previously attacking the MA, nobody did damage to them but you, and no mob likes to be slowed.  So you have 3 mobs hitting you for 400 or so damage once a tick (alotting to the 45% slow).  You can survive for how many ticks before the cleric needs to take time and mana away from the MA to cheal you? At 1200 damage a tick, I'd say 2 ticks at most (remember Cheal takes 10 seconds to cast), so in say 4 ticks, you have done measly damage to the mobs with MoM (the dot's not that great damage wise), and now all of a sudden, they see a cleric heal you for 3-4k damage.  NEW TARET!  Now the cleric has 3 mobs on her that are slowed 45% and doted.  At 1200 a tick damage, how long is a cleric going to survive?  You cannot mez the adds off the cleric because they are dotted for the rest of the cleric's short life.
<br />

<br />
Ok, this is hypothetical as I've never been so brave to use MoM as crowd control.  I'm not discounting your wonderful post, just the use of Mischief.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
