				<td colspan="2"><span>well ive been lurking here for a long time - and to be honest im pretty content with that<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> -  but i guess theres a time for evrything. I play a warrior 57 on luclin, as an extended break form my bard (56).
<br />
First off a good bard puller is clearly the best puller i can hope for in an ldon when i play my warrior. Those of you that bring in one new snared/slowed mob as the previous one is dying, while letting me know that it is incomming - thats priceless.
<br />

<br />
On the other hand some of you dont do this all that well (or you get untimely lull resists). So the bard will at times have the aggro of 3 mobs, I can not no ae taunt, and the bard here is often the only mezzer so his/her hp tend to plummet.. fast... with some bad luck, the bard dies (no not the bards with nice gear, virtue, who are calm enough to deftdance...), then the cleric (who tried to heal) get aggro from the 2 mobs im not fighting and it all becomes pretty messy.
<br />

<br />
As for warriors not pulling in LDOn (normal, lev 55ish), I have to disagree. As someone said even if you just hit the closest mob with an arrow you usually just get 2 sometimes 3 mobs, really not a problem at all for most groups. And once you get to a tricky room, lulling one or two is usually enough to safely pull. In addition (and with a little extra aggro, the only real benefit) when i make misstakes - I have the aggro - with evasive disciplines, warrior mitigation, hp/ac and against ldon mobs, i can stand 3-4 for quite a while, more than enough for mezz/root/peel and eventually a complete heal. Definatelly long enough for a controled evac.
<br />

<br />
So to conclude my ramblings..  yes clearly if a bard or paladin (or cleric or enchanter), want to, and know how to pull - By all means please do, but if you join a group where the warrior/sk/ranger/monk/bst was pulling, give them the benefit of the doubt, the group may have done a few very well executed missions before you came along, maybe they like the pace, maybe they prefer you as mezzer/melee/buffer (maybe they dont know you enough to trust you just yet =)) or maybe they just want you to /follow and sing manasong ;)
<br />
